      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Departmental distinction: Students majoring in Atmospheric Sciences can earn distinction, high distinction, and highest distinction upon graduation. The requirements for these awards are:"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "For distinction:  A minimum cumulative grade point average of 3.3 and have also completed an approved independent study project, approved senior thesis, or approved capstone."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "For high distinction: A minimum cumulative grade point average of 3.5 and have also completed an approved independent study project, approved senior thesis, or approved capstone."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "For highest distinction: A minimum cumulative grade point average of 3.7 and also completed an approved senior thesis or approved research capstone."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": "h4",
        "content": "General education: Students must complete the Campus General Education requirements including the campus general education language requirement."
      },
